  "decision_conditions": [
    "The development to which this permission relates must be begun no later than three years from the date of this decision notice.\r\rReason: To comply with the provision of Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990. \r",
    "The development hereby permitted shall be carried out in complete accordance with the approved plans and drawings listed in this decision notice, other than where those details are altered pursuant to conditions of this planning permission.\r\rReason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interests of proper planning. \r",
    "All new external work and finishes and work of making good shall match the original work in respect of the materials, colour, texture, profile and finished appearance, except where indicated otherwise on the drawings hereby approved or unless otherwise required by condition.\r\rReason: To preserve the character and appearance of the host building, the local area and wider Rectory Grove Conservation Area (Policies Q5, Q8, Q11 and Q22 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)). \r",
    "Notwithstanding the approved plans, all glazing bars for the replacement fenestration must be integrated and shall not be stuck on. \r\rReason: To preserve the character and appearance of the host building and wider Rectory Grove Conservation Area (Policies Q5, Q8, Q11 and Q22 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)). \r",
    "The flat roof of the lower ground floor extension hereby approved shall not be used as a roof terrace, sitting out area or other amenity space. \r\rReason: To protect the amenities of adjoining occupiers and the area (Policies Q2 and Q11 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)). \r\r",
    "Notwithstanding any indication given on the approved drawings, all rooflight hereby approved shall be of a traditional appearance set flush within the roof tiles and with a central glazing bar. \r\rReason: To ensure that the external appearance of the building is satisfactory and that it protects or enhances the character and appearance of the Rectory Grove Conservation Area (Policies Q5, Q8, Q11 and Q22 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)). \r",
    "If, within 5 years of the installation of the green roof(s), any planting forming part of the green roof shall die, be removed, or become seriously damaged or diseased, then this planting shall be replaced in the next planting season with a planting of similar size and species. \r\rReason: To safeguard the visual amenities of the area and to ensure that the development has an acceptable level of sustainability and biodiversity (Policies G1, G5 and SI 13 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies EN1, EN4, EN5, EN6, Q2, Q8 and Q9 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021)).\r"
  ],
